National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan met with Democratic Unionist Party leader Jeffrey Donaldson, Sinn Féin Party vice president Michelle O’Neill, and Sinn Féin Party leader Mary Lou McDonald. Sullivan praised the peace and progress achieved in Northern Ireland since the Belfast/Good Friday Agreement, affirming the United States' commitment to preserving and strengthening it. He condemned the recent attempted murder of a detective in Omagh and welcomed the cross-party denunciation of violence. The leaders discussed the importance of investing in Northern Ireland's economic potential and ensuring prosperity for all communities, expressing their willingness to work with U.S. Special Envoy to Northern Ireland for Economic Affairs Joe Kennedy III.